Application is a Free app developed and provided by Adianit at no cost and is intended for use as is.
This page informs users about our policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of Personal Information for anyone using our Service.
By using the Service, users agree to the collection and use of information according to this policy. The Personal Information collected is used for providing and improving the Service. Adianit will not use or share information except as described in this Privacy Policy.
1. Information Collection and Use
For a better experience while using our Service, certain personally identifiable information may be required. Any requested information will be retained on the user's device and is not collected by Adianit in any way.
The app uses third-party services that may collect information used to identify users:
Google Analytics for Firebase
Firebase Crashlytics
AdMob
Appodeal
Unity
2. Log Data
In case of errors in the app, data and information (through third-party products) called Log Data is collected. This may include device IP address, device name, OS version, app configuration, usage time and date, and other statistics.
3. Cookies
This Service does not use cookies explicitly. However, third-party code and libraries may use cookies to collect information and improve their services. You can choose to accept or refuse these cookies.
1. Data Controller
Adianit is the data controller responsible for your personal data. For any privacy-related concerns, please contact us at:
Email: support@adianit.com
2. Personal Data We Collect
2.1 Data collected automatically:
Device information (model, OS version, unique device identifiers)
IP address and location data
App usage statistics and behavior
Crash reports and performance data
Advertisement interactions
2.2 Data you provide to us:
Account information (if applicable)
In-app purchase information
Communication with our support team
User-generated content
3. Legal Basis for Processing
We process your personal data under the following legal bases:
Contractual necessity (to provide our services)
Legal obligations
Legitimate interests
Your consent (where applicable)
4. Third-Party Services
4.1 Firebase:
We use Firebase (Google LLC) for:
Analytics and performance monitoring
Crash reporting
User authentication (if applicable)
4.2 Advertising Partners:
Our advertising partners may collect data through:
Advertising identifiers
Cookie data
Usage information
5. Your Rights Under GDPR
You have the following rights:
Right to access your personal data
Right to rectification of inaccurate data
Right to erasure ("right to be forgotten")
Right to restrict processing
Right to data portability
Right to object to processing
Right to withdraw consent
6. Data Retention
We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, including legal, accounting, or reporting requirements.
7. International Data Transfers
Your data may be transferred to and processed in countries outside the European Economic Area (EEA). We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place through Standard Contractual Clauses and adequacy decisions.
8. Children's Privacy
This Service does not address anyone under 13. Adianit does not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. Parents or guardians who become aware that their child has provided personal information should contact Adianit for necessary actions.
9. Changes to This Policy
We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.
10. Data Protection Authority
You have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority if you believe we have not handled your personal data in accordance with applicable law.
